# First — What Problem Does CDC Solve?

Suppose at Amazon:

## customers table

| customer_id | city   |
| ----------- | ------ |
| C101        | Mumbai |

Later:

```text id="a4m9zx"
Mumbai -> Bangalore
```

Warehouse must know:

* what changed
* when it changed
* which rows changed

Without scanning entire table every time.

CDC solves this.

---

# What is CDC?

## Theory

**Change Data Capture (CDC)** is a technique used to identify and capture changes made to source data systems.

Changes include:

* INSERT
* UPDATE
* DELETE

---

# Simple Definition

CDC tracks only changed data instead of reprocessing full tables.

---

# Why CDC Is Important ⭐⭐⭐

Without CDC:

Every ETL run must:

```text id="u6k2wr"
Read entire table
```

Very expensive at scale.

Imagine:

* 10 billion rows
* only 100 changed rows

Full scan wastes:

* compute
* network
* time
* cloud cost

CDC avoids this.

---

# Real Example

## Source System

Before:

| customer_id | city   |
| ----------- | ------ |
| C101        | Mumbai |

---

After:

| customer_id | city      |
| ----------- | --------- |
| C101        | Bangalore |

CDC captures:

```text id="k8v5pq"
UPDATE:
customer_id = C101
old_city = Mumbai
new_city = Bangalore
```

Only changed row processed.

---

# Types of Changes CDC Captures

| Operation | Meaning              |
| --------- | -------------------- |
| INSERT    | new row added        |
| UPDATE    | existing row changed |
| DELETE    | row removed          |

---

