# Common CDC Approaches ⭐

# 1. Timestamp-Based CDC

Most common beginner approach.

---

## Idea

Source table contains:

```text id="p1x4mu"
last_updated_time
```

ETL loads rows where:

```sql id="j9r2tv"
last_updated_time > previous_run_time
```

---

# Example

| customer_id | city      | updated_at |
| ----------- | --------- | ---------- |
| C101        | Bangalore | 2026-01-10 |

Only latest rows fetched.

---

# Advantages

* simple
* easy implementation

---

# Disadvantages ⚠️

* may miss deletes
* depends on timestamps accuracy

---

# 2. Log-Based CDC ⭐⭐⭐

Most important enterprise method.

---

# Idea

Database transaction logs tracked directly.

Examples:

* MySQL binlog
* PostgreSQL WAL
* Oracle redo logs

CDC tools read logs continuously.

---

# Advantages ⭐

## 1. Real-Time Updates

Very fast.

---

## 2. Captures All Operations

Insert/update/delete.

---

## 3. No Full Table Scans

Highly scalable.

---

# Disadvantages

* more complex
* database-level setup required

---

# Real Tools Using CDC ⭐

| Tool         | Purpose               |
| ------------ | --------------------- |
| Debezium     | log-based CDC         |
| Apache Kafka | streaming transport   |
| AWS DMS      | migration + CDC       |
| Fivetran     | managed CDC pipelines |

