# 3. Trigger-Based CDC

Database triggers capture changes.

---

# Example

```text id="e5q8zl"
AFTER UPDATE trigger
```

writes changes into audit table.

---

# Problem

Triggers may slow transactional systems.

Less preferred at scale.

---

# CDC vs Full Load ⭐

| Full Load           | CDC                 |
| ------------------- | ------------------- |
| Entire table loaded | Only changes loaded |
| Expensive           | Efficient           |
| Slow                | Faster              |
| High compute cost   | Lower cost          |

